  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q95_TRAVEL_TIME_MIN
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>95. How long does it take you to travel from your house when going to the nearest primary care facility? (one-way, minutes)</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Gaano katagal ang iyong biyahe mula sa inyong bahay patungo sa pinakamalapit na primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Gurano kahalawig an byahe hali sa saindong harong paduman sa pinakaharaning pasildad?</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Unsa ka dugay ang biyahe gikan sa inyong balay padulong sa pinakaduol nga primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Unsa kadugay ang biyahe gikan sa imong balay paingon sa pinakaduol nga pasilidad sa primary care?</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Mationan-o kaiha an imo pagbiyahe tikang ha iyo balay kun makadto ha pinakahirani nga pasilidad han panguna nga pag-ataman?</p><p class="instruction">Please note the response for one way only from the time the respondent left their place of residence and arrived at the facility.</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q96_TRAVEL_COST_PHP
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>96. How much does it usually cost for you to travel to this facility from your home? (PHP, one-way)</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Magkano ang karaniwang nagagastos mo sa pagbiyahe mula sa inyong bahay papunta sa pasilidad na ito? Pakispecify sa Philippine pesos. Pakikumpirma ang ONE-WAY na gastos: mula sa bahay papunta sa pasilidad lamang para sa isang biyahe.</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Gurano man an tigaabot kan pamasahe paduman sa pasilidad hali sa saindong harong?</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Tagpila kasagaran ang gasto sa imong biyahe gikan sa inyong balay padulong niining pasilidad?</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Pila kasagaran ang gasto nimo sa pagbiyahe paingon niining pasilidad gikan sa inyong balay?</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Pira an kasagaran nga gastos para ha iyo pagbiyahe ngadto hini nga pasilidad tikang ha iyo balay?</p><p class="instruction">Please specify in Philippine pesos. Please confirm the ONE-WAY cost: from house to facility ONLY.</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q97_KNOWS_BOOKING
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>97. When you have a health problem, do you know how to book an appointment at a primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>Kapag may problema ka sa kalusugan, alam mo ba kung paano magpa-book ng appointment sa isang primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>Kun may health problem ka, aram mo ba kun pan-o magbook appointment sa primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>Kung naay problema sa panglawas, kabalo baka unsaon pagpahigayon ug appointment sa usa ka pasilidad?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>Kung aduna kay problema sa panglawas, kabalo ba ka unsaon pag-book og appointment sa usa ka primary care facility?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>In this section of the survey, I will now ask about how you access care in the last 6 months in a primary care facility. Examples of primary care facilities are RHUs, Health Center, and Barangay Health Station.</p><p>Kun mayda ka problema ha panlawas, maaram ka ba magpa-iskedyul hin appointment ha pasilidad para han una nga pag-antam han kahimsog?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for Access to a primary care facility. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q98_PHONE_ADVICE_OPEN
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>98. When your primary care facility is open, can you get advice quickly over the phone if you need it?</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Kapag bukas ang iyong primary care facility, nakakakuha ka ba agad ng payo sa pamamagitan ng telepono kung kinakailangan mo ito?</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Kun bukas an primary care facility, pwedeng makakuha advice sa telepono?</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Kung abre ang pasilidad, makakuha ka ba dayon ug tambag gamit imong selpon, kung kinahanglan na nimo kaau?</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Kung abli ang inyong primary care facility, makakuha ba ka dayon og tambag pinaagi sa telepono kung kinahanglan nimo?</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Kun abri na an iyo pasilidad han panguna nga pag-ataman, pwede ba kamo makakarawat hin sagdon dayon pinaagi han telepono kun kinahanglan niyo?</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q99_PHONE_ADVICE_CLOSED
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>99. When your primary care facility is closed, is there a phone number you can call when you get sick?</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Kapag sarado ang iyong primary care facility, mayroon ka bang numero ng telepono na maaari mong tawagan kapag ikaw ay nagkasakit?</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Kun sarado an primary care facility, may phone number ka pwedeng apudan?</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Kung sirado ang pasilidad, adunay bay number sa selpon nga matawagan kung magkasakit ka?</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Kung sirado ang inyong primary care facility, naa bay numero sa telepono nga pwede nimo tawagan kung magsakit ka?</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Kun sarado an iyo pasilidad han panguna nga pag-ataman, mayda ba numero han telepono nga matatawagan nga iyo matatawagan kun magkasakit kamo?</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q100_LEAVE_WORK_SCHOOL
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>100. When you have to visit your primary care facility, do you have to take a leave from work or school to go?</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Kapag kailangan mong bumisita sa iyong primary care facility, kailangan mo bang mag-leave sa trabaho o paaralan para makapunta?</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>Kun maduman ka sa primary care facility, kaipuhan mo bang mag-leave sa work o school?</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>Kung kinahanglan ka moadto sa imong primary care facility, kinahanglan ba ka mo-leave sa trabaho o eskwela?</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>Kung kinahanglan nimo mubisita sa inyong primary care facility, kinahanglan ba ka mokuha og leave sa trabaho o eskwelahan para makaadto?</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>Kun kinahanglan mo bumisita ha iyo pasilidad han panguna nga pag-ataman, kinahanglan mo ba mag-leave ha trabaho o eskwelahan para kumadto?</p>
  - name: HOUSEHOLDSURVEY_DICT.Q101_CHECKUP_FREQ
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>101. How often do you/your household member have a general check-up on your health (i.e., when you feel healthy, without any specific illness)?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>Gaano kadalas ka o ang miyembro ng iyong sambahayan ay nagpapasuri ng pangkalahatang kalusugan (hal. kapag pakiramdam ay malusog, walang partikular na sakit)?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>Pira ka beses ka o miembro kan saimong pamilya nagpapa general check-up sa saimong salud (hal. kun marhay an pakiramdam mo asin mayong espesipikong sakit)?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>Kasagaran, kapila ka o ang ubang miyembro sa imong pamilya magpa-general checkup maskin walay sakit nga ginabati?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>Unsa ka sagad ka/kamo sa inyong panimalay magpa-general check-up sa panglawas (kung himsog mo, walay espesipikong sakit)?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>We will now be asking about you and your household members’ actions taken for health concerns. This includes the type of services and facilities you access for your health and well-being.</p><p>Mationan-o kaagsob nga ikaw/imo kapamilya in mayda general check-up or general nga check-up han imo panlawas (i.e., kun san-o ka umabat hin kahimsog, waray bisan ano nga partikular nga sakit)?</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is for the Household members’ health-seeking behavior and outcomes. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies.</p>
